  "notes": "Mashhadi Persian (Mašhadī). Iran's second-largest city; capital of Khorasan. Urban Khorasani variety; prestige dialect of northeastern Iran. Conservative vowels (Khorasani base); some imāla in religious/Arabic vocabulary (pilgrimage city: shrine of Imam Reza). /q/ maintained in careful speech.",
